     {q:"Which type of microorganism generally needs a host to reproduce?", options:["A large mammal","A virus","A plant","A rock"], answer:1},
     {q:"Heredity involves the passing of traits through ___.", options:["Weather patterns","Ocean currents","Rock formations","Genes"], answer:3},
     {q:"Earthquakes are commonly linked to the movement of ___.", options:["Ocean currents only","Ratios","Clouds","Tectonic plates"], answer:3},
     {q:"Why is it valuable to review cells, microorganisms, genetics, and Earth systems together?", options:["Each topic must always be studied in isolation","These topics are entirely unrelated to each other","It helps connect and reinforce related science concepts learned across recent lessons","Review provides no benefit in science"], answer:2}
